 :tx/rationale "UAQ INSIGHT 4: CALIBRATION SPEEDUP — 5X DATA PER SESSION. Currently each system needs independent calibration data. R(t) needs task completion outcomes. ACP needs context usage feedback. F(S) needs boundary prediction errors. These are separate data streams. With unified A(t,x), every recommendation event (task shown, block presented, boundary measured) is a calibration data point for the SAME function. A session that produces 20 task events + 50 block presentations + 10 boundary measurements = 80 data points for one function vs 20/50/10 points for three separate functions. This means: (A) calibration converges in 3-5 sessions instead of 15-20. (B) External dog-food on a new project gets useful calibration within the FIRST session. (C) Cross-domain transfer via CRDT merge shares a SINGLE calibrated function, not five misaligned weight vectors. SPEC: ADR-FOUNDATION-018 (Hypothesis Ledger), ADR-FOUNDATION-024 (Learned Attention). VERIFICATION: After 3 sessions of external use, mean prediction error for ALL types should be below 0.15 (vs current 0.224 for task-only)."
